# SkyDexia Codespaces Replacement Blockers

This file names the code-backed blockers that still keep SkyDexia from being an autonomous Codespaces replacement. These are not tracker wishes. They are gaps visible in the current implementation.

## Mail continuity is now implemented

Current code evidence
- netlify/functions/skymail-send.js now queues outbound mail when provider configuration is missing or the adapter fails before a provider record is confirmed.
- netlify/functions/skymail-replay.js replays queued mail through the same send path.
- netlify/functions/skymail-status.js exposes queued mail and mail history by workspace.
- package.json now includes verify:mail-queue.
- scripts/verify-mail-queue.js proves queue, replay, and history behavior across restarts.
- scripts/verify-critical.js now includes verify:mail-queue.

Code implication
- Outbound communication now follows the same deferred continuity model as GitHub and Netlify release operations.
- Mail availability is no longer one of the blockers keeping SkyDexia from being a replacement-grade autonomous lane.

## Soak reliability is now executable proof

Current code evidence
- scripts/verify-soak.js now runs repeated runtime materialize, start, probe, task execution, log inspection, and stop cycles against the same workspace.
- The soak verifier asserts runtime state remains stable across repeated unattended cycles and that runtime audit records continue accumulating.
- package.json now includes verify:soak.
- scripts/verify-critical.js now includes verify:soak.

Code implication
- Repeated unattended runtime and task cycling is now proven in code instead of assumed from one-shot verifiers.
- Soak reliability is no longer one of the blockers keeping SkyDexia from a replacement-grade autonomy lane.

## No-gate autonomy fallback is now executable proof

Current code evidence
- scripts/verify-autonomy-fallback.js now starts SkyDexia with an unavailable gate endpoint and proves the agent returns a bounded local fallback result instead of failing closed.
- The verifier materializes the fallback node-api scaffold and smoke-tests the generated health endpoint.
- package.json now includes verify:autonomy-fallback and the aggregate verify:autonomy chain runs it.
- scripts/verify-critical.js now includes verify:autonomy-fallback.

Code implication
- The degraded autonomy lane is now exercised as executable proof, not treated as a documentation-only fallback.
- Gate outage is no longer one of the blockers keeping SkyDexia from a replacement-grade autonomy lane.

